{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πίθηκος</b> [ῐ], <br /> <i>Doric dialect</i> <b>πίθᾱκος</b>, ὁ, <b>ape, monkey</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th c.BC: Archilochus Lyricus 89.3, 91, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ichn.” 122, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 120, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 502a17: as _feminine_, πίθηκος μήτηρ 2nd c.AD: Babrius Fabularum Scriptor 56 \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]; πίθηκον ἐνδυομένην putting on <b>an ape's form</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 620c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; compare πιθήκη. <br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> nickname for a trickster, <b>jackanapes</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 907, “Av.” 440, “Ra.” 708, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; αὐτοτραγικὸς π., of Aeschines, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.242. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> proverbial, ἀντὶ λέοντος π. γίγνεσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 590b; ὑπὸ τῇ λεοντῇ πίθηκον περιστέλλειν 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Philops.” 5 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; π. ἐν πορφύρᾳ 'borrowed plumes', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.AD: Diogenianus Paroemiographus 7.94 \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]; ἐν πιθήκοις ὄντα δεῖ εἶναι π. 'in Rome we do as the Romans do', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Apollodorus Comicus 1.3 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ὄνος ἐν πιθήκοις 'parmi les aveugles le borgne est roi', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 402.8. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>dwarf</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 10th c.AD: Suidas Legal icographus \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> a ζῷον σελαχῶδες, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “De Natura Animalium - Ar.Byzantine Epit.” 12.27. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8791","accentedUnicode":"πίθηκος","shortDef":"ape","mediumDef":"ape","stepGloss":"ape","stepTransliteration":"pithēkos","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}